  urldate      = {2025-02-14},
  abstract     = {Men with prostate cancer often respond to androgen-deprivation therapy only to later relapse and develop lethal castration-resistant disease. Two models-adaptation and selection-have been described to explain how the disease progresses to this stage. In this Review, the authors describe each model and show that both models might contribute to advanced prostate cancer.},
  language     = {en},
  keywords     = {Cell signalling,Hormonal therapies,Mechanism of action,Prostate cancer},
  annotation   = {TLDR: Current research is focused on not only understanding the cellular mechanisms of CRPC, but also defining critical pathways that can be targeted with combinatorial therapies in castration-resistant cancer cells.\\
                  titleTranslation: 适应或选择——去势抵抗性前列腺癌的机制},
